<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1456,1874,2028]" lastBlockId="6.[811,1456,1937,2028]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3114493304" collectionCode="F, R" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="syntype">
<bibRefCitation author="DRAKE DEL CASTILLO E." box="[813,1079,1905,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref7472" refString="DRAKE DEL CASTILLO E. 1886. - Illustrationes Flora Insularum Maris Pacifici. G. Masson, Paris. 458 p., 50 tables. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 86930" type="book" year="1886">Drake Del Castillo (1886)</bibRefCitation>
cited two 
<typeStatus box="[1183,1263,1906,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">syntype</typeStatus>
collections, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Lépine 184</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[909,1052,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Nadeaud 343</emphasis>
(a mixed collection), both at Paris. 
<collectionCode box="[1437,1452,1938,1964]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[813,834,1970,1996]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">R</collectionCode>
. Fosberg proposed but never published this combination in his herbarium annotations of the 
<typeStatus box="[1228,1326,2002,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">syntypes</typeStatus>
. We hereby designate 
<emphasis box="[241,360,1937,1964]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Lépine 184</emphasis>
(2 sheets) as 
<typeStatus box="[510,611,1937,1963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">lectotype</typeStatus>
. This species is distinguished from other Tahiti congeners by a shortly pedunculate, 3-4-flowered inflorescence covered by spreading reddish-brown hairs, externally pilose campanulate calyx with short triangular to oblong lobes, pilose hypanthium and fruit, and white corollas with lobes puberulent distally (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1442,2001,2028]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[132,143,1786,1804]" captionTargetBox="[220,1367,215,1727]" captionTargetId="figure-90@2.[220,1367,215,1727]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tahitian Psychotria L. species: A, D, P. aff. speciosa, with truncate shortly-toothed calyx; B, C, P. trichocalyx (Drake) Fosberg ex J.-Y. Meyer, Lorence &amp; J. Florence, comb. nov.; B, inflorescence with bud and corolla at anthesis; C, young fruits and stipule (upper left); D, corolla in bud and expanded. A, D, Tahiti, Marau, J.-Y. Meyer photos; B, C, Tahiti, Atara, J.-Y. Meyer photos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4599029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4599029/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Fig. 1B, C</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
